                <mxCell id="DFD_LEGEND" value="&lt;b&gt;━━━ DFD OVERLAY LEGEND ━━━&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;i&gt;Template convention for all Tier-3 data-flow diagrams (diagrams/3-flows/data-flow/). Reuse this block in every DFD .drawio file.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;► CANVAS PRINCIPLE&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;This DFD uses the &lt;b&gt;full master architecture as visual canvas&lt;/b&gt; — every layer, component, and zone is preserved 1:1 from trackaroo-phase1-architecture.drawio. Vendors can map DFD elements back to the architecture by sight (same IDs, same colors, same positions). &lt;b&gt;Do NOT modify architecture cells&lt;/b&gt; — only add overlays on top.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;► SCOPE OF THIS FILE&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Survival Core (MOB-2000) · processes 1.0–7.0 mapped to MOB-2001 → MOB-2007. Out-of-scope components stay rendered as context but receive no DFD overlay.&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;► OVERLAYS ADDED ON TOP OF CANVAS&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;Process number prefix&lt;/b&gt; — Yourdon-style numbering (1.0, 2.0…) prepended to in-scope component labels&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;Data-flow edges&lt;/b&gt; — &lt;font color=&quot;#6a1b9a&quot;&gt;purple dotted&lt;/font&gt; (strokeColor=#6a1b9a, dashPattern=2 3) with &lt;b&gt;noun&lt;/b&gt; labels (payload name)&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;Prohibited paths&lt;/b&gt; — &lt;font color=&quot;#c62828&quot;&gt;red dashed&lt;/font&gt; (strokeColor=#c62828, dashPattern=5 5) labeled [X] PROHIBITED + named Rejection Trigger (RT-02, RT-05…)&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;Control/operational edges&lt;/b&gt; — solid grey/black with &lt;b&gt;verb&lt;/b&gt; labels (action conjugated for source)&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;► EDGE LABEL CONVENTIONS&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;TRIGGER:&lt;/b&gt; prefix on an edge label = event that initiates the destination process (user tap · GNSS fix arrival · sibling event emission · timer · OS event)&lt;br/&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;Bold &amp;lt;b&amp;gt; = primary noun (payload) or verb (action) · Italic &amp;lt;i&amp;gt; = context · timing · constraint · classification&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;► WHEN TO USE THIS TEMPLATE&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br/&gt;Each subsystem that needs data-flow visualisation gets its own DFD .drawio file in 3-flows/data-flow/. Steps for a new DFD: (1) copy the full architecture canvas, (2) copy this legend block, (3) update SCOPE OF THIS FILE line, (4) add process-number prefixes to in-scope components, (5) overlay data-flow / prohibited edges. Existing or planned files: &lt;b&gt;dfd-survival-core.drawio&lt;/b&gt; (this file) · &lt;b&gt;dfd-trackiq-pipeline.drawio&lt;/b&gt; (planned) · &lt;b&gt;dfd-ocs-pipeline.drawio&lt;/b&gt; (planned).&lt;br/&gt;&lt;br/&gt;&lt;b&gt;► CROSS-REFS&lt;/b&gt; Master architecture: ../../1-overview/trackaroo-phase1-architecture.drawio  ·  This DFD&#39;s narrative + tables: ./dfd-survival-core.md  ·  Visual style guide: ../../../CLAUDE.md" style="rounded=1;arcSize=2;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#fafafa;strokeColor=#616161;strokeWidth=1.5;dashed=1;dashPattern=5 3;verticalAlign=top;fontSize=11;align=left;spacingLeft=14;spacingTop=10;spacingRight=14;spacingBottom=10;" vertex="1" parent="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="20" y="2400" width="2100" height="340" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
            </root>
        </mxGraphModel>
    </diagram>
